title: Episode 130: Jordan Harbinger “The Larry King of Podcasting”
description:
On this episode, Robbie interviews his long time friend, Jordan Harbinger, an American radio personality, podcaster, voice actor, journalist, lawyer and businessman. They discuss his journey starting as a law student at the University of Michigan to becoming one of the most recognizable voices in podcasting who has conducted interviews with the likes of Kobe Bryant, Frank Abagnale, Malcolm Gladwell, Dennis Rodman and many other famous and successful individuals…

Jordan has hosted a top 50 iTunes podcast for over 12 years and receives over six million downloads per month, making The Jordan Harbinger Show one of the most popular podcasts in the world. The show was awarded Apple’s “Best of 2018” and is one of the most downloaded shows of the year. On The Jordan Harbinger Show, Jordan deconstructs the playbooks of the most successful people on earth and shares their strategies, perspectives, and practical insights with the rest of us.

Show Notes:
Jordan’s travel story of eating the beating heart of one of the most strange and deadly animals on the planet… (03:30)
How Jordan got into the world of dating and his thoughts on Double Your Dating… (07:00)
How Jordan got over his “Imposter Syndrome” at his first job on Wall Street… (09:00)
How to do something more interesting, work less and make more than everyone else in your office… (10:30)
Are you born with game or not? (12:10)
How “Naturals” come to be… (14:00)
Why it took Jordan and Robbie until their early 30’s to really reach a high level of value in the dating marketplace… (17:00)
The toxic mindset that will surely ruin your relationship with your dream girl… (18:15)
Is there hope for late bloomers (guys post 35) that are just getting into the world of dating and social dynamics? (19:30)
The good news for nerds and late bloomers… (20:45)
How Jordan hacked dating using a Michigan Law Hoodie… (21:45)
How Jordan grew a social circle of beautiful young women and used it to build a dating coaching business… (27:50)
The early days of the insanely popular “Jordan Harbinger Show” and how podcasting became a thing in 2006… (30:45)
Has the media of podcasting hit the masses or is there still room for growth? (32:45)
How advertising costs of podcasting compare to YouTube (this is shocking!)… (33:30)
How Jordan linked up with Adam Corolla and Dr. Drew of “Love Line” and transitioned out of dating and into mainstream media… (34:40)
When Jordan accidentally got Robbie’s dog blazed out of his mind… (38:00)
Links:
TheJordanHarbingerShow.com
Jordan Harbinger: Wikipedia
